                                            <div id="catfoot-inner">
                                                        <h2>Sleep and Sleepwear</h2><p>It is amazing to realise that, although humans spend an average of a third of their lifetime in the land of nod, most of us spend far less time choosing <a href="/sleepwear">sleepwear</a> than we do on the rest of our wardrobes. Experts agree that getting a good night's sleep is essential if we want to enjoy good health and vitality, so paying attention to creating a sleep-inducing environment is a priority. Using a supportive mattress is one of the number one tips for deep sleep, but this is something that isn't always a practical purchase. However, your sleepwear is also an important consideration, and one that you can upgrade today, without burning a hole in your pocket! Your sleepwear should be comfortable, correctly sized and make you feel good.
<h2>Sleepwear Outside of the Bedroom</h2><p>When lounging around or relaxing at home, many people enjoy slipping into their <b>sleepwear</b> for comfort. The latest sleepwear styles are stylish enough to answer the door to the pizza delivery man, or hang the washing out in, without you feeling under-dressed or lazy. Brands such as Gingerlilly and <a href="/lovable.htm">Lovable</a> add a touch of luxury to your sleepwear, so you feel smart enough to face the world....if you must!<h2>Sleepwear Styles</h2><p>For women, sleepwear can range from elegantly sexy <a href="/sleepwear">pyjama</a> sets, to beautiful <a href="/underwear/womens-underwear/chemise">chemises</a> or cute <a href="/clothes/mens-clothing/t-shirts">t-shirt</a> and short combinations. The most popular styles of <a href="/sleepwear/mens-sleepwear">men's sleepwear</a> are a lounge pant or shorts with a loose-fit t-shirt or <a href="/underwear/womens-underwear/singlets">singlet</a>. For children, two piece pyjama sets are a practical and appealing choice. <a href="/sleepwear/baby-sleepwear">Baby sleepwear</a> styles consist of all-in-one and romper suits, usually featuring easy open detailing for straight-forward nappy changes.<p>Looking to the latest fashions for sleepwear, the look of the moment features lots of soft, pastel colours combined with clear, bright tones. Floral patterns and lace or ribbon details add that feminine touch to <a href="/sleepwear/womens-sleepwear">women's sleepwear</a>, while men can work the classic look with masculine stripes. Baby sleepwear moves away from the typical blue for boys and pink for girls, with rich primary colours redefining the genre.
<h2>Indulge Yourself With Sleepwear</h2><p>Since <i>sleepwear</i> is one of the most intimate garments that you will ever wear, it is important to choose sensuous fabrics which feel good against your skin. For women look out for heavier fabric tops for opaque coverage. Lightweight cotton, silky satin and stretchy elastane will all offer a wonderfully comfortable sensation as you drift into dreamland or relax around your home.
                                            </div>
